        <div class="col-md-4"><p><h5>Once Word Herd has collected the significant words, it creates a network where words are the nodes, which are linked together if they appear in the same article.
        <br><br>
        Finally, Word Herd uses <a href="http://www.mapequation.org/code.html">Infomap</a> to analyze the network for clusters of words. These clusters loosely represent words that are more likely to appear with eachother than with those in the corpus as a whole.
        <br><br>
        The result is displayed for you in lists of words from each group. Words are ordered based on the "flow" of the word (which can be roughly understood as pagerank), and are sized based on their frequency within the corpus.
      </h5></p></div>
